7. TERMINATION PROCEDURES AND CONSEQUENCES.

Upon the occurrence of any of the following events, this Agreement may be terminated by either Party upon providing written notice to the other Party: (a) material breach of this Agreement by the other Party that remains uncured for thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice specifying the breach and requiring its remedy; or (b) the bankruptcy, insolvency, or reorganization under any applicable law of either Party. Upon termination for cause, the terminating Party shall not be obligated to make any further payments under this Agreement. However, all amounts owed prior to termination shall remain immediately due and payable in full, without any right of setoff, counterclaim or deduction. In the event of a termination not for cause, the Parties shall negotiate in good faith for a mutually agreeable transition period during which the terminated Party may wind down its obligations under this Agreement, subject to compliance with applicable law and regulations. The terminating Party shall have no liability for any claims or damages arising after the effective date of termination, except as otherwise provided herein. In the event of ambiguity in the interpretation of this Section 7, the Parties shall work together in good faith to achieve a mutually satisfactory resolution.
